                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "With these essays in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon\u2019s essay</strong>: \n<br><br>\n\n<div>\n\t <div style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12); background-color: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;\">\n    \n\t\t\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: #888; margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n\t\t  Brandon's essay\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div style=\"font-weight: bold; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\n\t\t  The conflict between convenience and sustainability\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div style=\"padding: 10px 14px; background-color: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7;\">\n\t\t\t<p>In today\u2019s fast-paced world, convenience often dominates daily choices, yet it frequently clashes with sustainability. Modern lifestyles prioritize speed and ease\u2014single-use plastics, fast fashion, and on-demand delivery epitomize this trend. These conveniences save time and effort but come at a significant environmental cost, contributing to pollution, resource depletion, and climate change. For example, the popularity of disposable packaging reduces the burden on consumers but increases landfill waste, undermining long-term ecological balance.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Sustainability, on the other hand, demands deliberate choices and often more effort: reusable products, energy-efficient practices, and mindful consumption require planning and patience. While these actions may seem inconvenient initially, they foster resilience and protect natural resources for future generations. The challenge lies in reconciling immediate comfort with long-term responsibility. Innovations such as eco-friendly packaging, renewable energy technologies, and sustainable urban design demonstrate that convenience and sustainability need not be mutually exclusive.\n</p>\n\t\t\t<p>Ultimately, achieving harmony between these priorities requires both systemic change and individual commitment. By rethinking habits, embracing responsible technologies, and valuing long-term ecological health over instant gratification, society can cultivate a lifestyle where convenience complements, rather than compromises, sustainability.\n</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div></div>",
                "DataExportTag": "Q5.2",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691454"
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691455",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "You will now edit Brandon's essay so that it reads convincingly as human-written and is unlikely...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "You will now edit Brandon's essay so that it reads convincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.&nbsp;<br>The essay is displayed below sentence by sentence, each followed by an editable text box prefilled with that sentence. Edit as many sentences as you like using the following rules.&nbsp;<br>To <b>revise wording</b>, edit the sentence directly in its box. To <b>merge sentences</b>, write the full merged sentence in the text box of the first sentence's box; leave the following merged sentence box(es) empty. To <b>split a sentence</b>, write all resulting sentences in the box of the original sentence. To <b>delete a sentence</b>, leave its box empty.&nbsp;<br>Make all changes you find appropriate before proceeding with the survey.&nbsp;<br>",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "QuestionType": "TE",
                "Selector": "ML",
                "DataVisibility": {
                    "Private": false,
                    "Hidden": false
                },
                "Configuration": {
                    "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
                },
                "QuestionDescription": "You will now edit Brandon's essay so that it reads convincingly as human-written and is unlikely...",
                "Validation": {
                    "Settings": {
                        "ForceResponse": "OFF",
                        "Type": "None"
                    }
                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "SearchSource": {
                    "AllowFreeResponse": "false"
                },
                "QuestionJS": "var qContainer;\nvar originalSentences; // global so addOnPageSubmit can access it\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function() {\n    qContainer = this.getQuestionContainer(); // assign to global\n\t\n\tvar title = \"The conflict between convenience and sustainability\";\n    originalSentences = [\n        \"In today\u2019s fast-paced world, convenience often dominates daily choices, yet it frequently clashes with sustainability.\",\n        \"Modern lifestyles prioritize speed and ease\u2014single-use plastics, fast fashion, and on-demand delivery epitomize this trend.\",\n        \"These conveniences save time and effort but come at a significant environmental cost, contributing to pollution, resource depletion, and climate change.\",\n\t\t\"For example, the popularity of disposable packaging reduces the burden on consumers but increases landfill waste, undermining long-term ecological balance.\",\n\t\t\"Sustainability, on the other hand, demands deliberate choices and often more effort: reusable products, energy-efficient practices, and mindful consumption require planning and patience.\",\n\t\t\"While these actions may seem inconvenient initially, they foster resilience and protect natural resources for future generations.\",\n\t\t\"The challenge lies in reconciling immediate comfort with long-term responsibility.\",\n\t\t\"Innovations such as eco-friendly packaging, renewable energy technologies, and sustainable urban design demonstrate that convenience and sustainability need not be mutually exclusive.\",\n\t\t\"Ultimately, achieving harmony between these priorities requires both systemic change and individual commitment.\",\n\t\t\"By rethinking habits, embracing responsible technologies, and valuing long-term ecological health over instant gratification, society can cultivate a lifestyle where convenience complements, rather than compromises, sustainability.\"\n    ];\n\n    // hide default Qualtrics input\n    var defaultInput = qContainer.querySelector(\"textarea\");\n    defaultInput.style.display = \"none\";\n\t\n\t// create container for custom sentence boxes\n    var textEntryContainer = document.createElement(\"div\");\n    defaultInput.parentNode.appendChild(textEntryContainer);\n\t\n\t// display title\n\tvar titleEl = document.createElement(\"h3\");\n\ttitleEl.textContent = title;\n\ttitleEl.style.marginBottom = \"15px\";\n\ttextEntryContainer.appendChild(titleEl);\n    \n    // render one editable box per sentence\n    originalSentences.forEach(function(sentence, idx) {\n\t\tvar wrapper = document.createElement(\"div\");\n\t\twrapper.style.marginBottom = \"20px\";\n\t\twrapper.style.padding = \"16px 20px\";\n\t\twrapper.style.borderRadius = \"8px\";\n\t\twrapper.style.boxShadow = \"0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12)\";\n\t\twrapper.style.backgroundColor = \"#ffffff\";\n\t\twrapper.style.border = \"1px solid #e0e0e0\";\n\n\t\t// sentence number header\n\t\tvar header = document.createElement(\"div\");\n\t\theader.style.fontWeight = \"600\";\n\t\theader.style.fontSize = \"13px\";\n\t\theader.style.textTransform = \"uppercase\";\n\t\theader.style.letterSpacing = \"0.05em\";\n\t\theader.style.color = \"#888\";\n\t\theader.style.marginBottom = \"12px\";\n\t\theader.textContent = \"Sentence \" + (idx + 1);\n\t\twrapper.appendChild(header);\n\n\t\t// original sentence \u2014 grey pill background (non-editable display)\n\t\tvar origDiv = document.createElement(\"div\");\n\t\torigDiv.style.marginBottom = \"10px\";\n\t\torigDiv.style.padding = \"8px 12px\";\n\t\torigDiv.style.backgroundColor = \"#f5f5f5\";\n\t\torigDiv.style.borderRadius = \"4px\";\n\t\torigDiv.style.fontSize = \"15px\";\n\t\torigDiv.style.lineHeight = \"1.5\";\n\t\tvar origLabel = document.createElement(\"div\");\n\t\torigLabel.style.fontSize = \"11px\";\n\t\torigLabel.style.fontWeight = \"600\";\n\t\torigLabel.style.textTransform = \"uppercase\";\n\t\torigLabel.style.color = \"#aaa\";\n\t\torigLabel.style.marginBottom = \"4px\";\n\t\torigLabel.textContent = \"Original\";\n\t\torigDiv.appendChild(origLabel);\n\t\torigDiv.appendChild(document.createTextNode(sentence));\n\t\twrapper.appendChild(origDiv);\n\n\t\t// editable textarea label\n\t\tvar editLabel = document.createElement(\"div\");\n\t\teditLabel.style.fontSize = \"11px\";\n\t\teditLabel.style.fontWeight = \"600\";\n\t\teditLabel.style.textTransform = \"uppercase\";\n\t\teditLabel.style.color = \"#5b9bd5\";\n\t\teditLabel.style.marginBottom = \"6px\";\n\t\teditLabel.textContent = \"Your edit\";\n\t\twrapper.appendChild(editLabel);\n\n\t\t// editable textarea\n\t\tvar textarea = document.createElement(\"textarea\");\n\t\ttextarea.value = sentence;\n\t\ttextarea.rows = 2;\n\t\ttextarea.style.width = \"100%\";\n\t\ttextarea.style.boxSizing = \"border-box\";\n\t\ttextarea.style.padding = \"8px 10px\";\n\t\ttextarea.style.border = \"1px solid #ddd\";\n\t\ttextarea.style.borderRadius = \"4px\";\n\t\ttextarea.style.fontSize = \"14px\";\n\t\ttextarea.style.resize = \"vertical\";\n\t\ttextarea.style.fontFamily = \"inherit\";\n\t\ttextarea.style.backgroundColor = \"#f0f6ff\";\n\t\ttextarea.className = \"sentenceBox\";\n\t\ttextarea.dataset.index = idx;\n\t\twrapper.appendChild(textarea);\n\n\t\ttextEntryContainer.appendChild(wrapper);\n\t});\n\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnPageSubmit(function() {\n    var resultPairs = [];\n\n    qContainer.querySelectorAll(\".sentenceBox\").forEach(function(box) {\n        var orig = originalSentences[parseInt(box.dataset.index, 10)]; \n        var edited = box.value.trim();\n        resultPairs.push({ orig: orig, edited: edited });\n    });\n\n    var json = JSON.stringify(resultPairs);\n\tconsole.log(\"Saving EditPairsJSON:\", json);\n\tQualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(\"EditPairsJSON\", btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(json))));\n});",
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "You will now edit Brandon's essay so that it reads convincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.&nbsp;<br>The essay is displayed below sentence by sentence, each followed by an editable text box prefilled with that sentence. Edit as many sentences as you like using the following rules.&nbsp;<br>To <b>revise wording</b>, edit the sentence directly in its box. To <b>merge sentences</b>, write the full merged sentence in the text box of the first sentence's box; leave the following merged sentence box(es) empty. To <b>split a sentence</b>, write all resulting sentences in the box of the original sentence. To <b>delete a sentence</b>, leave its box empty.&nbsp;<br>Make all changes you find appropriate before proceeding with the survey.&nbsp;<br>",
                "DataExportTag": "Q5.3",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691455"
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691456",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. Explain each change you...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. Explain&nbsp;each change you made in the box below each pair.",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "QuestionType": "TE",
                "Selector": "ML",
                "DataVisibility": {
                    "Private": false,
                    "Hidden": false
                },
                "Configuration": {
                    "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
                },
                "QuestionDescription": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. Explain each change you...",
                "Validation": {
                    "Settings": {
                        "ForceResponse": "OFF",
                        "Type": "None"
                    }
                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "SearchSource": {
                    "AllowFreeResponse": "false"
                },
                "QuestionJS": "var qContainer;\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function() {\n    qContainer = this.getQuestionContainer();\n\n    var raw = \"${e://Field/EditPairsJSON}\";\n\n    if (!raw) {\n        console.log(\"EditPairsJSON is empty\");\n        return;\n    }\n\n    var pairs;\n    try {\n        var json = decodeURIComponent(escape(atob(raw)));\n        pairs = JSON.parse(json);\n    } catch(e) {\n        console.log(\"Decode/parse failed:\", e, \"| Raw:\", raw);\n        return;\n    }\n\n    // hide default Qualtrics input\n    var defaultInput = qContainer.querySelector(\"textarea\");\n    defaultInput.style.display = \"none\";\n\n    // create main container\n    var container = document.createElement(\"div\");\n    defaultInput.parentNode.appendChild(container);\n\n    // word-level diff helper\n    function wordDiff(orig, edited) {\n        var origWords = orig.split(\" \");\n        var editedWords = edited.split(\" \");\n        var result = document.createDocumentFragment();\n\n        var m = origWords.length, n = editedWords.length;\n        var dp = [];\n        for (var i = 0; i <= m; i++) {\n            dp[i] = [];\n            for (var j = 0; j <= n; j++) dp[i][j] = 0;\n        }\n        for (var i = 1; i <= m; i++)\n            for (var j = 1; j <= n; j++)\n                dp[i][j] = origWords[i-1] === editedWords[j-1]\n                    ? dp[i-1][j-1] + 1\n                    : Math.max(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1]);\n\n        var ops = [], i = m, j = n;\n        while (i > 0 || j > 0) {\n            if (i > 0 && j > 0 && origWords[i-1] === editedWords[j-1]) {\n                ops.unshift({ type: \"keep\", word: editedWords[j-1] });\n                i--; j--;\n            } else if (j > 0 && (i === 0 || dp[i][j-1] >= dp[i-1][j])) {\n                ops.unshift({ type: \"add\", word: editedWords[j-1] });\n                j--;\n            } else {\n                ops.unshift({ type: \"remove\", word: origWords[i-1] });\n                i--;\n            }\n        }\n\n        ops.forEach(function(op, k) {\n            var span = document.createElement(\"span\");\n            span.textContent = (k > 0 ? \" \" : \"\") + op.word;\n            if (op.type === \"add\") {\n                span.style.backgroundColor = \"#c6efce\";\n                span.style.borderRadius = \"3px\";\n                span.style.padding = \"0 2px\";\n            } else if (op.type === \"remove\") {\n                span.style.backgroundColor = \"#ffc7ce\";\n                span.style.textDecoration = \"line-through\";\n                span.style.borderRadius = \"3px\";\n                span.style.padding = \"0 2px\";\n                span.style.color = \"#888\";\n            }\n            result.appendChild(span);\n        });\n\n        return result;\n    }\n\n    // render one block per sentence pair\n    pairs.forEach(function(pair, idx) {\n        var isModified = pair.orig !== pair.edited;\n\n        var wrapper = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        wrapper.style.marginBottom = \"20px\";\n        wrapper.style.padding = \"16px 20px\";\n        wrapper.style.borderRadius = \"8px\";\n        wrapper.style.boxShadow = \"0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.12)\";\n        wrapper.style.backgroundColor = \"#ffffff\";\n        wrapper.style.border = \"1px solid #e0e0e0\";\n\n        // header\n        var header = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        header.style.fontWeight = \"600\";\n        header.style.fontSize = \"13px\";\n        header.style.textTransform = \"uppercase\";\n        header.style.letterSpacing = \"0.05em\";\n        header.style.color = \"#888\";\n        header.style.marginBottom = \"12px\";\n        header.textContent = \"Sentence \" + (idx + 1);\n        wrapper.appendChild(header);\n\n        // original sentence\n        var origDiv = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        origDiv.style.marginBottom = \"8px\";\n        origDiv.style.padding = \"8px 12px\";\n        origDiv.style.backgroundColor = \"#f5f5f5\";\n        origDiv.style.borderRadius = \"4px\";\n        origDiv.style.fontSize = \"15px\";\n        origDiv.style.lineHeight = \"1.5\";\n        var origStrong = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        origStrong.style.fontSize = \"11px\";\n        origStrong.style.fontWeight = \"600\";\n        origStrong.style.textTransform = \"uppercase\";\n        origStrong.style.color = \"#aaa\";\n        origStrong.style.marginBottom = \"4px\";\n        origStrong.textContent = \"Original\";\n        origDiv.appendChild(origStrong);\n        origDiv.appendChild(document.createTextNode(pair.orig));\n        wrapper.appendChild(origDiv);\n\n        // edited sentence\n        var editedDiv = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        editedDiv.style.marginBottom = \"14px\";\n        editedDiv.style.padding = \"8px 12px\";\n        editedDiv.style.backgroundColor = isModified ? \"#f0fff4\" : \"#f5f5f5\";\n        editedDiv.style.borderRadius = \"4px\";\n        editedDiv.style.fontSize = \"15px\";\n        editedDiv.style.lineHeight = \"1.5\";\n        var editedStrong = document.createElement(\"div\");\n        editedStrong.style.fontSize = \"11px\";\n        editedStrong.style.fontWeight = \"600\";\n        editedStrong.style.textTransform = \"uppercase\";\n        editedStrong.style.color = isModified ? \"#4caf7d\" : \"#aaa\";\n        editedStrong.style.marginBottom = \"4px\";\n        editedStrong.textContent = isModified ? \"Your edit\" : \"Unchanged\";\n        editedDiv.appendChild(editedStrong);\n        editedDiv.appendChild(wordDiff(pair.orig, pair.edited));\n      \n        wrapper.appendChild(editedDiv);\n\n        // explanation label + box only if modified\n        if (isModified) {\n            var label = document.createElement(\"div\");\n            label.style.fontSize = \"13px\";\n            label.style.fontWeight = \"600\";\n            label.style.marginBottom = \"6px\";\n            label.style.color = \"#555\";\n            label.textContent = \"Why did you make this change?\";\n            wrapper.appendChild(label);\n\n            var explanationBox = document.createElement(\"textarea\");\n            explanationBox.rows = 3;\n            explanationBox.style.width = \"100%\";\n            explanationBox.style.boxSizing = \"border-box\";\n            explanationBox.style.padding = \"8px 10px\";\n            explanationBox.style.border = \"1px solid #ddd\";\n            explanationBox.style.borderRadius = \"4px\";\n            explanationBox.style.fontSize = \"14px\";\n            explanationBox.style.resize = \"vertical\";\n            explanationBox.style.fontFamily = \"inherit\";\n            explanationBox.className = \"explanationBox\";\n            explanationBox.dataset.index = idx;\n            wrapper.appendChild(explanationBox);\n        }\n\n        container.appendChild(wrapper);\n    });\n});\n\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnPageSubmit(function() {\n    var explanations = [];\n\n    qContainer.querySelectorAll(\".explanationBox\").forEach(function(box) {\n        explanations.push({\n            index: parseInt(box.dataset.index, 10), // which sentence pair this belongs to\n            explanation: box.value.trim()\n        });\n    });\n\n    Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(\"EditExplanationsJSON\", JSON.stringify(explanations));\n});",
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. Explain&nbsp;each change you made in the box below each pair.",
                "DataExportTag": "Q5.4",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691456"
            }
        },
