                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>Egypt's parliament has approved a long-debated agreement transferring sovereignty over two Red Sea islands, Tiran and Sanafir, to Saudi Arabia, marking a significant step in a controversial maritime deal. Lawmakers voted in favor of the accord during a plenary session, despite vocal opposition from some MPs and public protests in recent years.</p>\n           <p>The government has argued that the islands historically belong to Saudi Arabia and that the agreement corrects administrative arrangements dating back to the 1950s. Officials said the transfer would strengthen bilateral ties and unlock economic cooperation, including planned development projects in the Red Sea.</p>\n           <p>Critics, however, contend that the islands are Egyptian territory and have challenged the move in court. Previous judicial rulings had produced conflicting decisions, fueling a heated national debate over sovereignty and transparency. Security officials emphasized that navigation through the strategic Strait of Tiran will remain open in accordance with international agreements.</p>\n           <p>Saudi authorities welcomed the vote, describing it as a reaffirmation of historic rights and regional partnership. The agreement now awaits final ratification procedures, after which administrative control is expected to be formally transferred.</p>\n           <p>Analysts say the decision could reshape regional alliances and test domestic political stability in the months ahead. Across the region.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>Skywatchers around the world are preparing for one of nature\u2019s most breathtaking events: a solar eclipse. But how much do you really know about this celestial phenomenon?</p>\n           <p>A solar eclipse occurs when the Moon passes between the Earth and the Sun, temporarily blocking some or all of the Sun\u2019s light. There are three main types: total, partial, and annular. During a total solar eclipse, the Moon completely covers the Sun, turning day into twilight for a few dramatic minutes. In a partial eclipse, only part of the Sun is obscured. An annular eclipse happens when the Moon is too far from Earth to fully cover the Sun, leaving a bright \u201cring of fire\u201d visible in the sky.</p>\n           <p>Solar eclipses do not happen every month because the Moon\u2019s orbit is slightly tilted relative to Earth\u2019s orbit around the Sun. When conditions align perfectly, the spectacle can be seen from specific regions of the world.</p>\n           <p>Experts warn that looking directly at a solar eclipse without proper eye protection can cause serious eye damage. Special eclipse glasses or indirect viewing methods are essential.</p>\n           <p>Beyond their beauty, solar eclipses help scientists study the Sun\u2019s outer atmosphere, known as the corona, offering valuable insights into solar activity and space weather.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>A growing number of companies are migrating to cloud computing platforms, and new research suggests that fear of being left behind is a major driver. According to a recent industry survey, 81% of business leaders say their organization\u2019s cloud investments are influenced by concerns about \u201cmissing out\u201d on innovation, competitive advantage, or industry momentum.</p>\n           <p>While cost savings, scalability, and flexibility remain commonly cited benefits of cloud adoption, the study indicates that competitive pressure now plays an equally powerful role. Executives report feeling compelled to modernize IT systems as rivals adopt artificial intelligence tools, data analytics platforms, and remote collaboration technologies built on cloud infrastructure.</p>\n           <p>Analysts say this \u201cfear of missing out,\u201d or FOMO, reflects a broader shift in corporate strategy. Rather than waiting for clear returns on investment, companies are increasingly making proactive technology bets to avoid falling behind faster-moving competitors. In some sectors, particularly finance, retail, and healthcare, cloud adoption is viewed as essential for digital transformation.</p>\n           <p>However, experts caution that rushed migrations can create new risks, including cybersecurity vulnerabilities and spiraling costs. They advise firms to pair cloud enthusiasm with clear planning and governance.</p>\n           <p>Ultimately, the cloud has become less of a technical upgrade and more of a strategic necessity\u2014driven as much by perception and pressure as by measurable gains.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
        {
