                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>Uber Technologies is facing a significant leadership shake-up following the release of an internal investigation into workplace misconduct and compliance failures, company officials confirmed Tuesday. The months-long probe, launched after a series of employee complaints and regulatory inquiries, uncovered lapses in oversight, inconsistent enforcement of company policies, and failures in reporting procedures.</p>\n           <p>As a result, three senior executives, including the head of regional operations, have stepped down, while two others have been placed on administrative leave pending further review. The company\u2019s board said it has appointed an interim compliance chief and will form a new ethics committee to strengthen accountability measures.</p>\n           <p>Chief Executive Dara Khosrowshahi said in a statement that the findings were \u201cdeeply concerning\u201d and pledged to implement sweeping reforms. \u201cWe are committed to rebuilding trust with our employees, drivers, riders, and regulators,\u201d he said. \u201cThis moment demands transparency and decisive action.\u201d</p>\n           <p>The investigation also prompted renewed scrutiny from transportation regulators in several major cities, where Uber\u2019s operating licenses are subject to periodic review. Industry analysts say the shake-up could temporarily disrupt operations but may ultimately position the company for more stable growth if reforms are effectively implemented.</p>\n           <p>Uber shares closed down 3 percent following the announcement.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>Jimmy Wales, cofounder of Wikipedia, says the online encyclopedia he helped launch 25 years ago needs a radical overhaul \u2014 and he believes blockchain technology could provide it. Speaking at a technology conference this week, Wales argued that Wikipedia\u2019s volunteer-driven model has struggled with declining editor participation, opaque governance disputes and growing mistrust over content moderation.</p>\n           <p>Under his proposal, articles and edits would be recorded on a public blockchain, creating a transparent, tamper-resistant history of every contribution. Contributors could earn digital tokens for verified edits, potentially providing financial incentives to attract subject-matter experts. Smart contracts might also be used to manage disputes and automate editorial decisions according to community-approved rules.</p>\n           <p>Wales contends that decentralization would reduce the power of small administrator groups and make it harder for coordinated misinformation campaigns to manipulate entries. Critics, however, question whether blockchain systems can scale to handle Wikipedia\u2019s vast traffic and warn that token incentives could encourage low-quality edits.</p>\n           <p>The Wikimedia Foundation said it is reviewing emerging technologies but remains committed to its nonprofit mission and community governance. Whether blockchain can truly replace Wikipedia\u2019s current infrastructure remains uncertain, yet the debate underscores mounting pressure to reinvent one of the internet\u2019s most trusted resources globally.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>Across Canada and the United States, Indigenous communities are reclaiming traditional birth practices that were suppressed for generations. Once outlawed or discouraged by colonial policies that forced women into distant hospitals, community-led midwifery is returning to reserves and rural homelands.</p>\n           <p>Elders and knowledge keepers are teaching young midwives ancestral teachings that center birth as a sacred ceremony rather than a medical emergency. Expectant mothers are again surrounded by family, language, song, and land. In northern Manitoba, a new Indigenous-run birthing center reports that more than 60 families have chosen to deliver locally since it opened last year, reducing costly medical evacuations and strengthening cultural continuity.</p>\n           <p>Health researchers say outcomes are promising. Community-based prenatal care has improved maternal mental health and increased breastfeeding rates. Advocates argue the movement is not a rejection of modern medicine but a blending of clinical training with traditional knowledge.</p>\n           <p>Federal and provincial agencies have begun funding Indigenous midwifery programs, acknowledging past harms. For many families, however, the revival is about sovereignty as much as safety \u2014 restoring the right to welcome children into the world according to their own laws, lands, and lifeways. Leaders say the resurgence signals healing across generations and renewed community strength nationwide.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
