                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>The Nobel Peace Prize was awarded today to the International Campaign for Nuclear Abolition, honoring its decades-long effort to eliminate atomic weapons and reduce the risk of catastrophic war. The Norwegian Nobel Committee praised the coalition of grassroots activists, scientists, and survivors of nuclear testing for building global momentum behind the Treaty on the Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons. In its citation, the committee said the group had \"reframed the debate on nuclear deterrence by highlighting the humanitarian consequences of any use.\"</p>\n           <p>Accepting the award in Oslo, executive director Maria Santos called the prize \"a tribute to ordinary people who refuse to live under the shadow of annihilation.\" She urged nuclear-armed states to join disarmament talks and invest instead in health, climate, and education. Leaders from several countries welcomed the decision, while officials in nuclear powers cautioned that deterrence remains essential to national security.</p>\n           <p>Analysts said the prize could intensify diplomatic pressure ahead of next year's nonproliferation review conference, where divisions between nuclear and non-nuclear states are expected. Founded in 2007, the campaign now includes more than 600 partner organizations worldwide and has focused on survivor testimony and youth activism. Committee chair Anne Lunde said the honor recognizes \"persistent moral leadership.\"</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>On May 30th, several landmark moments shaped the legacy of WMMO, marking the date as one of reflection and celebration for listeners and staff alike. In 1985, WMMO officially flipped its format to classic rock, a bold move that distinguished the station in a competitive market and set the tone for decades of legendary programming. The debut song that morning\u2014The Rolling Stones\u2019 \u201cStart Me Up\u201d\u2014signaled a new era that resonated with Central Florida audiences.</p>\n           <p>Years later, on May 30, 1999, WMMO hosted its first annual Memorial Weekend Rock Marathon, a 48-hour, commercial-light tribute to rock\u2019s greatest icons. The event quickly became a fan-favorite tradition, drawing record-breaking listenership and cementing the station\u2019s reputation for immersive, fan-driven programming.</p>\n           <p>May 30th also marks a milestone from 2012, when WMMO launched its revamped mobile app, expanding its reach beyond terrestrial radio and connecting with a new generation of digital listeners. The app\u2019s debut included exclusive backstage interviews and live concert streams, underscoring the station\u2019s commitment to innovation.</p>\n           <p>From format-defining decisions to community-building broadcasts, May 30th stands as a testament to WMMO\u2019s enduring dedication to classic rock and the loyal audience that continues to turn it up loud.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>A growing number of China\u2019s most prominent business leaders have vanished from public view in recent years, fueling speculation about the forces reshaping the country\u2019s corporate elite. Once-celebrated tycoons who dominated headlines, from technology pioneers to real estate magnates, have abruptly stepped down from executive roles, disappeared from social media, or been detained without immediate explanation.</p>\n           <p>Analysts point to Beijing\u2019s sweeping anti-corruption campaigns and regulatory crackdowns as key factors. Authorities have tightened oversight of industries ranging from finance and technology to property development, citing concerns about systemic risk and national security. In several high-profile cases, executives later reemerged to acknowledge investigations into alleged financial crimes or regulatory violations. Others have faced formal charges, while a few have remained largely out of sight.</p>\n           <p>The uncertainty has rattled investors and prompted questions about transparency in the world\u2019s second-largest economy. International markets have reacted sharply to sudden leadership changes at major firms, underscoring the global impact of domestic policy shifts.</p>\n           <p>Chinese officials maintain that the investigations are necessary to promote \u201ccommon prosperity\u201d and ensure long-term stability. But for many observers, the recurring pattern of disappearing tycoons highlights the precarious balance between private enterprise and state authority in modern China.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
